msContents.summary: 1 slightly disordered copy of the Qurʼān

msItem.title: al-Qurʼān
القرآن
msItem.note: The folios are somewhat disordered. The last sūrah features in folio 6a, and not in the last folio of this copy (483b), which contains part of the first sūrah.
msItem.incipit: fol.3a.1 سورة ڡاٿحه الكٿٿ مكية وهى سبع ايات الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ رَبّ الْعَلَمِينَ الرَّحْمَںِ الرَّحِيم . ملك يوْم الديں
msItem.explicit: fol.6b.6 فُلَ اَعُوذُ بِرَبِّ اِلنَّاسِ مَلِكِ اِلنَّاسِ اِلَهِ اِلنَّاسِ مِں شَرِّ الْوَسْوَاسِ الْخَنَّاسِ الَّذِى يُوَسْوِسُ ڢِى صُدورِ النَّاسِ مِںَ نَّةِ وَالنَّاسِ

decoDesc.decoNote: There is some decoration on fol. 2a

list.item: Fol.6a.1 Note affirming that the Qur'an is the word of God.
Fol.484a.1 Note on the benefits and the merits of certain Qur'anic verses.
